pma:database.name: techshopjava
pma:database.pma:table: CREATE TABLE `cart` ( `serial` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `C_USERNAME` varchar(10) NOT NULL, `PRODUCT_ID` varchar(9) NOT NULL, `QUANTITY` int(11) NOT NULL DEFAULT 1, `ADDED_DATE` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT current_timestamp(), PRIMARY KEY (`serial`), KEY `C_USERNAME` (`C_USERNAME`), KEY `PRODUCT_ID` (`PRODUCT_ID`), CONSTRAINT `cart_ibfk_1` FOREIGN KEY (`C_USERNAME`) REFERENCES `customer` (`C_USERNAME`), CONSTRAINT `cart_ibfk_2` FOREIGN KEY (`PRODUCT_ID`) REFERENCES `products` (`PRODUCT_ID`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=237 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_general_ci;
pma:database.pma:view: CREATE ALGORITHM=UNDEFINED DEFINER=`root`@`localhost` SQL SECURITY DEFINER VIEW `techshopjava`.`cartdetails` AS select `p`.`PRODUCT_NAME` AS `PRODUCT_NAME`,`c`.`QUANTITY` AS `QUANTITY`,`p`.`PRICE` AS `PRICE`,`p`.`VAT` AS `VAT`,round(`c`.`QUANTITY` * `p`.`PRICE`,3) AS `TOTAL_PRICE`,round(`c`.`QUANTITY` * `p`.`PRICE` * `p`.`VAT` / 100,3) AS `VAT_AMOUNT`,`c`.`C_USERNAME` AS `C_USERNAME` from (`techshopjava`.`cart` `c` join `techshopjava`.`products` `p`) where `c`.`PRODUCT_ID` = `p`.`PRODUCT_ID`;
pma:database.pma:table: CREATE TABLE `customer` ( `C_USERNAME` varchar(10) NOT NULL, `CUSTOMER_NAME` varchar(20) NOT NULL, `PHONE_NO` int(15) NOT NULL, `EMAIL` varchar(30) NOT NULL, `ADDRESS` varchar(30) NOT NULL, `PASSWORD` varchar(11) NOT NULL, `DATE_REGISTERED` date NOT NULL DEFAULT current_timestamp(), PRIMARY KEY (`C_USERNAME`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_general_ci;

CREATE TABLE `employee` ( `empID` varchar(5) NOT NULL, `empEmail` varchar(100) NOT NULL, `empPhone` varchar(15) NOT NULL, `empName` varchar(100) NOT NULL, `empPassword` varchar(255) NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`empID`), UNIQUE KEY `empEmail` (`empEmail`), UNIQUE KEY `empPhone` (`empPhone`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_general_ci;

CREATE TABLE `orderlist` ( `orderID` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `paymentID` int(11) DEFAULT NULL, `C_USERNAME` varchar(10) DEFAULT NULL, `orderDate` date DEFAULT NULL, `product_list` varchar(1000) NOT NULL, `total_price` varchar(15) DEFAULT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`orderID`), KEY `paymentID` (`paymentID`), KEY `C_USERNAME` (`C_USERNAME`), CONSTRAINT `orderlist_ibfk_1` FOREIGN KEY (`paymentID`) REFERENCES `payment` (`paymentID`), CONSTRAINT `orderlist_ibfk_2` FOREIGN KEY (`C_USERNAME`) REFERENCES `customer` (`C_USERNAME`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=35 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_general_ci;

CREATE TABLE `payment` ( `paymentID` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `cartID` int(11) NOT NULL, `c_username` varchar(50) NOT NULL, `payment_date` date NOT NULL, `payment_method` enum('bkash','card','cash on delivery','not paid') NOT NULL DEFAULT 'not paid', `totalPaid` decimal(15,2) DEFAULT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`paymentID`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=66 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_general_ci;

CREATE TABLE `products` ( `PRODUCT_ID` varchar(9) NOT NULL, `PRODUCT_NAME` varchar(255) NOT NULL, `BRAND` varchar(255) NOT NULL, `CATEGORY` varchar(255) NOT NULL, `PRICE` decimal(10,2) NOT NULL, `VAT` decimal(3,2) DEFAULT 0.00, `AVAILABLE_QUANTITY` int(11) NOT NULL, `SOLD` int(11) NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`PRODUCT_ID`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_general_ci;

CREATE TABLE `supplier` ( `supplierid` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `suppliername` varchar(255) NOT NULL, `supplieremail` varchar(255) NOT NULL, `supplierbrand` varchar(255) NOT NULL, `productId` varchar(9) DEFAULT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`supplierid`), KEY `productId` (`productId`), CONSTRAINT `supplier_ibfk_1` FOREIGN KEY (`productId`) REFERENCES `products` (`PRODUCT_ID`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=71 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_general_ci;
